L58X1AA-1 04/06/2026 JC (L) LG 2025-3707 SUB HB98
29 A BILL
30 TO BE ENTITLED
31 AN ACT
32
33 Relating to scholarships; to establish a program to
34 grant tuition money to eligible dependents of law enforcement
35 officers for use in participating public institutions of
36 higher education in the State of Alabama; to provide
37 requirements for scholarship eligibility; to provide
38 scholarship conditions and terms; to provide for
39 administration of the program by the Alabama Commission on
40 Higher Education; to establish the Alabama Law Enforcement
41 Officers' Family Scholarship Fund; and to establish a
42 distinctive blackout license plate to fund the scholarship
43 program.
44 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
45 Section 1. Article 11, commencing with Section
46 36-21-220, is added to Chapter 21 of Title 36, Code of Alabama
47 1975, to read as follows:
48 Article 11.
49 §36-21-220
50 This article shall be known and cited as the Alabama
51 Law Enforcement Officers' Family Scholarship Program.
52 §36-21-221
53 As used in this article, the following terms have the
54 following meanings:
55 (1) ACADEMIC PERIOD. A semester or quarter.
56 (2) APPROVED POSTSECONDARY PROGRAM. Any for-credit or
