57 noncredit workforce or career training program or course of
58 study at the undergraduate level directed toward a vocational
59 certification, an associate degree, or a bachelor's degree
60 offered by a participating institution. The term includes an
61 academic major.
62 (3) COMMISSION. The Alabama Commission on Higher
63 Education, including the commission's Office of Student
64 Assistance.
65 (4) ELIGIBLE DEPENDENT. An individual who, on the date
66 of applying for the scholarship provided under this article,
67 is:
68 a. Not eligible for the police officers' survivors
69 educational assistance provided under Article 5 of this
70 chapter; and
71 b. Either of the following:
72 1. A natural or adopted child of a qualifying law
73 enforcement officer, who is under 24 years of age and who has
74 resided in the state for at least the five preceding years.
75 2. The current or surviving spouse of a qualifying law
76 enforcement officer who has resided in the state for at least
77 the five preceding years.
78 (5) LAW ENFORCEMENT AGENCY. Any law enforcement
79 department or agency that serves the state, a municipality, a
80 county, or a postsecondary educational institution.
81 (6) PARTICIPATING INSTITUTION. An accredited public
82 postsecondary vocational school, technical school, community
83 or junior college, college, or university that enters into a
84 contract with the commission to accept reimbursement for a
Page 3

contract with the commission to accept reimbursement for a
L58X1AA-1 04/06/2026 JC (L) LG 2025-3707 SUB HB98
85 scholarship awarded to an eligible dependent.
86 (7) QUALIFYING LAW ENFORCEMENT OFFICER. The term
87 includes any law enforcement officer, as defined in Section
88 13A-11-38:
89 a. Who, on or after January 1, 2026, is employed
90 full-time for at least 15 years by a law enforcement agency in
91 the state; or
92 b. Who, having been employed full-time for at least 15
93 years by a law enforcement agency in the state, has been
94 separated for no more than 10 years from full-time employment
95 as a law enforcement officer due to resignation, retirement,
96 or death, unless the individual was terminated from final
97 employment as a law enforcement officer pursuant to a
98 disciplinary action.
99 (8) TUITION AND MANDATORY FEES. Costs charged for
100 tuition and mandatory fees that are assessed for all students
101 at the participating institution. The term does not include
102 differential tuition or department-specific or course-specific
103 fees, or books, equipment, or supplies.
104 §36-21-222
105 (a) The Alabama Law Enforcement Officers' Family
106 Scholarship is established to pay on behalf of eligible
107 dependents the cost of tuition and mandatory fees for up to
108 eight semesters or 12 quarters in an approved postsecondary
109 program.
110 (b)(1) The scholarship shall pay tuition and mandatory
111 fees after any other amounts from public or private
112 scholarships, grants, aid, or gifts awarded by third parties
Page 4

scholarships, grants, aid, or gifts awarded by third parties
