113 to the eligible dependent for the academic period have been
114 applied.
115 (2)a. The amount for each recipient shall be capped at
116 two thousand five hundred dollars ($2,500) for each academic
117 period.
118 b. Notwithstanding paragraph a., if the recipient
119 qualifies for a discount on tuition and mandatory fees because
120 the recipient's eligibility is based upon the qualifying law
121 enforcement officer's employment by a law enforcement agency
122 that serves a postsecondary institution, the amount shall be
123 capped at one thousand five hundred dollars ($1,500) for each
124 academic period. This amount may be used for tuition and
125 mandatory fees at any participating institution.
126 (c) The scholarship may be granted to as many
127 dependents of one qualifying law enforcement officer as are
128 eligible and who comply with the requirements of this article.
129 (d) The scholarship shall be administered by the
130 commission.
131 (e)(1) Availability of the scholarship to eligible
132 dependents is conditioned, pursuant to Section 36-21-227, on
133 funds available in the Alabama Law Enforcement Officers'
134 Family Scholarship Fund.
135 (2) Reimbursement from the Alabama Law Enforcement
136 Officers' Family Scholarship Fund shall be made at the end of
137 each academic period by the commission to a participating
138 institution by certified invoice submitted by the institution
139 that is substantiated by the name of each student receiving
140 the scholarship, with the amount claimed for each student.
