144 §36-21-223
145 The scholarship application by an eligible dependent
146 shall be submitted to the commission and include, but not be
147 limited to, the following:
148 (1) Documentation from the participating institution
149 that the applicant has been accepted for admission and is
150 enrolled as a student.
151 (2) A copy of a completed Free Application for Federal
152 Student Aid (FAFSA) submitted to the United States Department
153 of Education, or documentation from the participating
154 institution that the applicant has completed a FAFSA.
155 (3) Documentation, as determined by rules adopted by
156 the commission, that a spouse or parent is a qualifying law
157 enforcement officer.
158 (4) In the case of a dependent who is a current or
159 surviving spouse, a certified copy of the marriage certificate
160 to a qualifying law enforcement officer.
161 (5) In the case of a dependent who is a natural or
162 adopted child, a certified copy of the birth certificate or
163 the decree of adoption showing the parental relationship to a
164 qualifying law enforcement officer.
165 (6) A signed Family Educational Rights and Privacy Act
166 (FERPA) release form.
167 §36-21-224
168 (a) Approval for the scholarship shall be granted to an
