199 §36-21-225
200 (a) The responsibilities of the commission include, but
201 may not be limited to, the following:
202 (1) Receive scholarship applications.
203 (2) Make determinations on scholarship eligibility.
204 (3) Waive scholarship requirements as provided in this
205 article.
206 (4) Enter into and administer contracts with
207 participating institutions.
208 (5) Develop the necessary forms to administer the
209 program.
210 (6) Publicize the scholarship by written materials or
211 electronic means and accept donations.
212 (b) The commission is authorized to charge a fee of no
213 more than three percent of the monies deposited to the credit
214 of the Alabama Law Enforcement Officers' Family Scholarship
215 Fund in a fiscal year for administering this article.
216 (c) The commission is authorized to adopt rules to
217 implement, administer, and interpret the requirements of this
218 article.
