236 §36-21-227
237 (a) The Alabama Law Enforcement Officers' Family
238 Scholarship Fund is created in the State Treasury. All monies
239 received by the commission from any source as provided in
240 subsections (b) or (c) or pursuant to Section 2 shall be
241 deposited into the State Treasury to the credit of the fund.
242 Amounts deposited into the fund shall be budgeted and allotted
243 in accordance with Sections 41-4-80 through 41-4-96 and
244 Sections 41-19-1 through 41-19-12.
245 (b)(1) Availability of the scholarship to eligible
246 dependents, beginning with the fiscal year that starts on
247 October 1, 2027, shall be subject to an annual appropriation
248 in the Education Trust Fund Appropriation Act which shall not
249 exceed ten million dollars ($10,000,000). This provision does
250 not affect the availability of scholarships from funds
251 provided on hand prior to October 1, 2027.
252 (2) The annual appropriation provided in subdivision
